### OTP API Testing

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@userId = test-user-123
@email = test@example.com

### 1. Send OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### 2. Verify OTP (Replace XXXXXX with actual OTP from email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "otpCode": "XXXXXX"
}

### 3. Cleanup Expired OTPs (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/cleanup
Content-Type: application/json

### Test with Invalid Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "test-user-456",
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

### Test with Empty UserId
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Test Verify with Invalid OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "otpCode": "000000"
}
